Roslyn Baatjies, Netwerk24St Mark and St John Anglican Church (via Facebook) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Port Elizabeth - A robber asked a priest at an Anglican church in Port Elizabeth to pray for him as he made off with congregants' cellphones and money,&nbsp;Netwerk24&nbsp;reported. The armed robber threatened the priest and 11 members of the St Mark and St John Anglican Church in Van der Kemp Street just after 10:00 on Saturday, police spokesperson Captain Sandra Janse van Rensburg said. He was dressed in a grey and black hoodie and wore sunglasses.The robber walked from pew to pew, demanding cellphones and money. A camera was also taken.He then apparently asked the priest to pray for him before he left.No-one was injured during the incident. Police are investigating a case of armed robbery.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.